# SoftDent data pull (universal)

Whenever SoftDent desktop is used to pull financial or report data (aging, register, collections, daysheet, transactions, claims, or any other SoftDent report):

## Allowed Output Options only

1. **Excel** — select Excel → Enter → complete SoftDent Setup / save flow. Prefer for money beams and morning bundle.
2. **Print Preview** — select Print Preview → Enter → read the **last page** for totals when Excel is unavailable.

## Forbidden

- **Never Printer** — if SoftDent waits on a printer dialog, Cancel (`Alt+C`). Do not OK a print job.
- **Never File** — do not use SoftDent “File” / invent Select File Name paths under `C:\SoftDentReportExports` in the SoftDent UI.
- **Never invent dollars** — empty export ≠ `$0` (`emptyNotZero`).
- **Never SoftDent write-back** — read-only pulls only.

## Defaults

- Launch SoftDent only via **CS SoftDent Software.lnk** (`-sus`), never bare `SDWIN.EXE`.
- Sign On: prefer `SOFTDENT_SIGNON_*` / `SOFTDENT_GUI_*` when set; else **`COMPUTE`** / **`computer`** (lowercase, case-sensitive).
- SoftDent UI: keyboard or mouse only. **Never Esc** on SoftDent main (quit prompt).
- Next-business-day money reports: pull at **9:00 PM local the night before**.

## Agents / automation

- GUI export code and HAL playbooks must enforce Excel | Print Preview only.
- If Excel is greyed: run attended Excel enablement runbook / probe — do not fall through to Printer or File.
- After Excel save, SoftDent may open a temp workbook — SaveCopyAs to the office export folder as documented; do not invent SoftDent’s Select File Name directory.
